— Maps slot index to player via cumulative entry ranges\n- `verifyLordRound(event, players)` — Validates round fairness against on-chain RoundSettled event\n- `calculateJackpotPayout(tier, totalEntries)` — Returns `(entryAmount * totalEntries) * 0.97`\n\n**Types:**\n- `LordPlayerEntry` — {player: PublicKey, entries: number}\n- `RoundSettledEvent` — Event data structure matching on-chain log\n- `LordVerificationResult` — {valid, errors, computedWinningSlot?, computedWinner?}\n\n## 3. Anchor Client Exports — `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/index.ts`\n\n**Exports:**\n- `CoinflipIDL` — Coinflip program IDL (JSON)\n- `LordofrngsIDL` — Lord of the RNGs program IDL (JSON)\n- `PlatformIDL` — Platform program IDL (JSON)\n- Type exports: `Coinflip`, `Lordofrngs`, `Platform` (TypeScript types for IDE support)\n\n---\n\n**For your chain.ts**: You'll want to use the instruction names (snake_case in IDL), the PDA derivation functions, and the RoundSettled event shape. The tier/round_number pattern with little-endian encoding is consistent across all instructions."}],"totalDurationMs":13251,"totalTokens":40682,"totalToolUseCount":3,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":15599,"cache_read_input_tokens":24087,"output_tokens":989,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":15599,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PpR1XHVwszHNSdBdwX8Tmx","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary document for you. Let me compile all the information:\n\n## Exploration Complete: Lord of the RNGs Frontend Code Structure\n\nI've thoroughly explored the Lord of the RNGs frontend codebase. Here's the complete structure and current mock implementation:\n\n---\n\n### **Directory Structure**\n\n```\nsources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/\n├── components/\n│   ├── ActiveRoundView.tsx          # Active game wheel view\n│   ├── CountdownTimer.tsx           # Countdown timer display\n│   ├── TierLobby.tsx                # Tier selection lobby\n│   ├── TierRoundView.tsx            # Tier status card\n│   ├── WheelVisualization.tsx       # Main wheel animation/rendering\n│   └── index.ts                     # Component exports\n├── context/\n│   └── LordOfRngsContext.tsx        # React context + provider (state management)\n├── utils/\n│   ├── mock-simulation.ts           # MOCK IMPLEMENTATION (needs replacement)\n│   └── odds.ts                      # Odds calculation utilities\n├── types.ts                         # Type definitions\n└── index.ts                         # Public API exports\n```\n\n---\n\n### **1. Core Types (`types.ts`)**\n\n```typescript\n// Round phases: waiting → countdown → spinning → revealing → complete\nexport type RoundPhase = \"waiting\" | \"countdown\" | \"spinning\" | \"revealing\" | \"complete\";\n\nexport interface Round {\n  id: string;\n  tier: Tier;                    // Iron, Bronze, Silver, Gold, Emerald, Diamond\n  entryAmount: number;           // Cost per entry in SOL\n  phase: RoundPhase;\n  players: PlayerEntry[];        // Array of players + their entry counts\n  totalEntries: number;\n  poolAmount: number;            // Total SOL in pool\n\n  // Timing\n  createdAt: number;\n  countdownStartedAt?: number;\n  countdownEndsAt?: number;\n  completedAt?: number;\n\n  // Result (after spin)\n  winningSlot?: number;          // 0-indexed winning slot\n  winner?: string;               // Winner's address\n  payoutAmount?: number;         // 97% of pool (3% fee)\n  claimed?: boolean;             // Claimed status\n\n  // Provably Fair - VRF\n  seedHash: string;              // SHA-256 of server seed (public before spin)\n  serverSeed?: string;           // Revealed after settlement\n  vrfProof?: string;             // VRF proof for verification\n  blockHash?: string;            // Solana blockhash used as entropy\n}\n\nexport interface PlayerEntry {\n  address: string;\n  entries: number;               // Number of slots owned\n  displayName?: string;\n  color: string;                 // Color for wheel visualization\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **2. Mock Simulation (`mock-simulation.ts`) - NEEDS REPLACEMENT**\n\n**This file contains all mock functions that must be replaced with real chain calls:**\n\n#### **Mock Store & Timers**\n```typescript\n// Lines 16-32: In-memory mock store (all timer-based)\ninterface MockStore {\n  rounds: Map<string, Round>;\n  tierRounds: Map<Tier, string>;\n  listeners: Map<string, Set<(round: Round) => void>>;\n  mockPlayerTimers: Map<string, TimerId[]>;\n}\n\n// Line 92: Server seeds stored in memory (revealed after settlement)\nconst serverSeeds = new Map<string, { serverSeed, blockHash, vrfProof }>();\n```\n\n#### **Key Mock Functions (Need On-Chain Replacement)**\n\n| Function | Current Behavior | Needs Replacement With |\n|----------|------------------|----------------------|\n| `createRound(tier)` | Creates round in memory with fake fair data | On-chain `initialize_round` instruction |\n| `joinRound(tier, addr, entries)` | Adds player to in-memory round | On-chain `join_round` instruction |\n| `buyMoreEntries(roundId, addr, entries)` | Updates entries in memory | On-chain `buy_more_entries` instruction |\n| `startCountdown(roundId)` | Timer-based phase transition | On-chain `start_countdown` (or auto-trigger on 2nd player) |\n| `startSpinning(roundId)` | Random winner selection (MOCK!) | On-chain `start_spin` instruction with VRF callback |\n| `resolveRound(roundId)` | Calculates winner from random slot | Callback handler when VRF proof arrives |\n| `subscribeToRound(roundId, callback)` | In-memory listeners | Subscribe to on-chain event stream (Bankrun/RPC) |\n| `initializeMockRounds()` | Creates mock rounds at startup | Query on-chain for active rounds per tier |\n\n#### **Mock Players (Automation - Can Stay as Client-Side)**\n```typescript\n// Lines 355-427: Mock players join rounds automatically\n- scheduleMockPlayers(roundId)           // 1-3 mock players join randomly\n- scheduleMockPlayersDuringCountdown()   // 2-5 more during countdown\n- addMockPlayer(roundId)                 // Single mock player addition\n- cancelMockPlayerTimers()               // Cancel pending timers on spin\n```\n\nThese are **client-side automation** for testing/demo purposes — can stay but should be toggleable.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Context (`LordOfRngsContext.tsx`)**\n\n**State Management:**\n```typescript\ninterface LordOfRngsContextValue {\n  // State\n  activeRound: Round | null;            // Current active round\n  tierStatuses: TierStatus[];           // All tier status cards\n  userHistory: Round[];                 // User's completed rounds\n  selectedTier: Tier | null;            // Tier selection\n  entryCount: number;                   // Entry count input\n\n  // Loading states\n  loading: boolean;\n  joining: boolean;                     // Joining transaction in flight\n  buyingMore: boolean;                  // Buy more entries transaction\n  claiming: boolean;                    // Claim payout transaction\n\n  // Actions\n  joinTierRound: () => Promise<void>;          // Join with selectedTier + entryCount\n  buyMoreEntriesAction: (entries) => Promise<void>;\n  claimPayout: () => Promise<void>;\n  leaveRound: () => void;\n  refreshRounds: () => void;             // Refresh all tier statuses\n}\n```\n\n**Key Effects:**\n1. **Initialize** (lines 104-110): Calls `initializeMockRounds()` → needs to query chain instead\n2. **Poll** (lines 112-118): Every 2s calls `refreshRounds()` → should subscribe to events instead\n3. **Subscribe** (lines 120-161): Subscribes to active round updates via `subscribeToRound()` → needs chain subscription\n4. **Join Round** (lines 164-189): Calls mock `joinRound()` → needs on-chain TX\n5. **Buy More** (lines 191-213): Calls mock `buyMoreEntries()` → needs on-chain TX\n6. **Claim Payout** (lines 215-240): Auto-claims on win → needs on-chain TX\n\n---\n\n### **4. Utilities**\n\n#### **Odds Calculation (`odds.ts`)**\n- ✅ **No mock here** — all deterministic math\n- Uses \"largest remainder method\" for fair rounding\n- Returns `PlayerOdds[]` with exact percentages summing to 100%\n- Used by wheel visualization to size player slots\n\n#### **Helper Functions (`mock-simulation.ts`)**\n```typescript\ntruncateAddress(address: string)         // Truncates address for display\ngetPlayerColor(index, isCurrentUser)     // Assigns colors from PLAYER_COLORS array\ncalculatePayout(poolAmount: number)      // Returns poolAmount * 0.97\ngenerateMockAddress()                    // Random address format (for mock players)\ngenerateMockHexString(length)            // Random hex for fair data (MOCK)\ngenerateFairnessData()                   // Generates fake seed/proof/blockhash (MOCK)\n```\n\n---\n\n### **5. Spec Contract (`docs/specs/101-lord-of-the-rngs/spec.md`)**\n\n**Key Requirements from Spec:**\n\n1. **Tier Amounts**: SOL values from `game-engine/types.ts` (0.005–1.0 SOL per tier)\n2. **Max Players**: 20 per round\n3. **Min Players to Start**: 2 unique players\n4. **Countdown Duration**: 60 seconds\n5. **Spin Trigger**: Any player can trigger after countdown expires (idempotent)\n6. **Winner Selection**: VRF determines slot (0 to totalEntries-1)\n7. **Payout**: 97% of pool (3% fee)\n8. **Claim Model**: Pull-based (`claim_payout` instruction)\n\n**Phases:**\n- **Waiting**: No countdown yet, joining enabled\n- **Countdown**: 60s timer, joining enabled, additional entries allowed\n- **Spinning**: Wheel animating, no new entries\n- **Revealing**: Show winner before auto-transition\n- **Complete**: Round settled, winner can claim\n\n---\n\n### **6. Components Overview**\n\n| Component | Purpose | Depends On |\n|-----------|---------|-----------|\n| `TierLobby.tsx` | Grid of 6 tier cards | `tierStatuses`, `setSelectedTier` |\n| `TierRoundView.tsx` | Individual tier status card | `TierStatus` type |\n| `ActiveRoundView.tsx` | Main game view when in round | `Round`, `WheelVisualization` |\n| `WheelVisualization.tsx` | Animated wheel rendering | `Round`, `calculateOdds()` |\n| `CountdownTimer.tsx` | 60s countdown display | `endsAt` timestamp |\n\n---\n\n### **Summary: What Needs Replacement**\n\n| Item | Current | Target |\n|------|---------|--------|\n| **Round Creation** | `createRound()` timer-based | `initialize_round` on-chain instruction |\n| **Join Round** | `joinRound()` in-memory | `join_round` on-chain instruction |\n| **Buy Entries** | `buyMoreEntries()` in-memory | `buy_more_entries` on-chain instruction |\n| **Phase Transitions** | `startCountdown()`, `startSpinning()` timer-based | On-chain instructions + event handlers |\n| **Winner Selection** | Random number (MOCK) | VRF callback result |\n| **Subscriptions** | In-memory listeners | Event stream subscription (RPC/Bankrun) |\n| **Auto-Claim** | Instant UI update | On-chain `claim_payout` TX + confirmation |\n| **Mock Players** | Can stay or be made toggleable | Client-side automation (optional) |\n\n---\n\n### **File Paths (Absolute)**\n\n- **Types**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/types.ts`\n- **Mock Simulation**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/utils/mock-simulation.ts`\n- **Context**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/context/LordOfRngsContext.tsx`\n- **Odds**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/utils/odds.ts`\n- **Components**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/components/`\n- **Spec**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/101-lord-of-the-rngs/spec.md`\n\nThis exploration reveals a clean mock architecture ready for chain integration. The main replacement work is connecting the context's async action functions to real on-chain instructions and replacing the in-memory store with on-chain state queries."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aaa25a1 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 47438\ntool_uses: 13\nduration_ms: 40136</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8e5d7c3d-ef66-4971-8f66-de7d7c43ed7c","uuid":"23e08b0e-d8ad-493f-a516-0ed6ff5913f9","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the existing Lord of the RNGs frontend code structure. Please find and read:\n\n1. All files in `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/` — especially types.ts, context file, and mock-simulation.ts\n2. The directory structure of the lord-of-rngs feature folder\n\nReturn the full content of:\n- types.ts (or similar types file)\n- mock-simulation.ts (or similar mock file)  \n- The context file (LordOfRngsContext.tsx or similar)\n- Any utils/ directory contents\n\nFocus on understanding what mock functions exist that need to be replaced with real chain calls.","agentId":"aaa25a1","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary document for you. Let me compile all the information:\n\n## Exploration Complete: Lord of the RNGs Frontend Code Structure\n\nI've thoroughly explored the Lord of the RNGs frontend codebase. Here's the complete structure and current mock implementation:\n\n---\n\n### **Directory Structure**\n\n```\nsources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/\n├── components/\n│   ├── ActiveRoundView.tsx          # Active game wheel view\n│   ├── CountdownTimer.tsx           # Countdown timer display\n│   ├── TierLobby.tsx                # Tier selection lobby\n│   ├── TierRoundView.tsx            # Tier status card\n│   ├── WheelVisualization.tsx       # Main wheel animation/rendering\n│   └── index.ts                     # Component exports\n├── context/\n│   └── LordOfRngsContext.tsx        # React context + provider (state management)\n├── utils/\n│   ├── mock-simulation.ts           # MOCK IMPLEMENTATION (needs replacement)\n│   └── odds.ts                      # Odds calculation utilities\n├── types.ts                         # Type definitions\n└── index.ts                         # Public API exports\n```\n\n---\n\n### **1. Core Types (`types.ts`)**\n\n```typescript\n// Round phases: waiting → countdown → spinning → revealing → complete\nexport type RoundPhase = \"waiting\" | \"countdown\" | \"spinning\" | \"revealing\" | \"complete\";\n\nexport interface Round {\n  id: string;\n  tier: Tier;                    // Iron, Bronze, Silver, Gold, Emerald, Diamond\n  entryAmount: number;           // Cost per entry in SOL\n  phase: RoundPhase;\n  players: PlayerEntry[];        // Array of players + their entry counts\n  totalEntries: number;\n  poolAmount: number;            // Total SOL in pool\n\n  // Timing\n  createdAt: number;\n  countdownStartedAt?: number;\n  countdownEndsAt?: number;\n  completedAt?: number;\n\n  // Result (after spin)\n  winningSlot?: number;          // 0-indexed winning slot\n  winner?: string;               // Winner's address\n  payoutAmount?: number;         // 97% of pool (3% fee)\n  claimed?: boolean;             // Claimed status\n\n  // Provably Fair - VRF\n  seedHash: string;              // SHA-256 of server seed (public before spin)\n  serverSeed?: string;           // Revealed after settlement\n  vrfProof?: string;             // VRF proof for verification\n  blockHash?: string;            // Solana blockhash used as entropy\n}\n\nexport interface PlayerEntry {\n  address: string;\n  entries: number;               // Number of slots owned\n  displayName?: string;\n  color: string;                 // Color for wheel visualization\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **2. Mock Simulation (`mock-simulation.ts`) - NEEDS REPLACEMENT**\n\n**This file contains all mock functions that must be replaced with real chain calls:**\n\n#### **Mock Store & Timers**\n```typescript\n// Lines 16-32: In-memory mock store (all timer-based)\ninterface MockStore {\n  rounds: Map<string, Round>;\n  tierRounds: Map<Tier, string>;\n  listeners: Map<string, Set<(round: Round) => void>>;\n  mockPlayerTimers: Map<string, TimerId[]>;\n}\n\n// Line 92: Server seeds stored in memory (revealed after settlement)\nconst serverSeeds = new Map<string, { serverSeed, blockHash, vrfProof }>();\n```\n\n#### **Key Mock Functions (Need On-Chain Replacement)**\n\n| Function | Current Behavior | Needs Replacement With |\n|----------|------------------|----------------------|\n| `createRound(tier)` | Creates round in memory with fake fair data | On-chain `initialize_round` instruction |\n| `joinRound(tier, addr, entries)` | Adds player to in-memory round | On-chain `join_round` instruction |\n| `buyMoreEntries(roundId, addr, entries)` | Updates entries in memory | On-chain `buy_more_entries` instruction |\n| `startCountdown(roundId)` | Timer-based phase transition | On-chain `start_countdown` (or auto-trigger on 2nd player) |\n| `startSpinning(roundId)` | Random winner selection (MOCK!) | On-chain `start_spin` instruction with VRF callback |\n| `resolveRound(roundId)` | Calculates winner from random slot | Callback handler when VRF proof arrives |\n| `subscribeToRound(roundId, callback)` | In-memory listeners | Subscribe to on-chain event stream (Bankrun/RPC) |\n| `initializeMockRounds()` | Creates mock rounds at startup | Query on-chain for active rounds per tier |\n\n#### **Mock Players (Automation - Can Stay as Client-Side)**\n```typescript\n// Lines 355-427: Mock players join rounds automatically\n- scheduleMockPlayers(roundId)           // 1-3 mock players join randomly\n- scheduleMockPlayersDuringCountdown()   // 2-5 more during countdown\n- addMockPlayer(roundId)                 // Single mock player addition\n- cancelMockPlayerTimers()               // Cancel pending timers on spin\n```\n\nThese are **client-side automation** for testing/demo purposes — can stay but should be toggleable.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Context (`LordOfRngsContext.tsx`)**\n\n**State Management:**\n```typescript\ninterface LordOfRngsContextValue {\n  // State\n  activeRound: Round | null;            // Current active round\n  tierStatuses: TierStatus[];           // All tier status cards\n  userHistory: Round[];                 // User's completed rounds\n  selectedTier: Tier | null;            // Tier selection\n  entryCount: number;                   // Entry count input\n\n  // Loading states\n  loading: boolean;\n  joining: boolean;                     // Joining transaction in flight\n  buyingMore: boolean;                  // Buy more entries transaction\n  claiming: boolean;                    // Claim payout transaction\n\n  // Actions\n  joinTierRound: () => Promise<void>;          // Join with selectedTier + entryCount\n  buyMoreEntriesAction: (entries) => Promise<void>;\n  claimPayout: () => Promise<void>;\n  leaveRound: () => void;\n  refreshRounds: () => void;             // Refresh all tier statuses\n}\n```\n\n**Key Effects:**\n1. **Initialize** (lines 104-110): Calls `initializeMockRounds()` → needs to query chain instead\n2. **Poll** (lines 112-118): Every 2s calls `refreshRounds()` → should subscribe to events instead\n3. **Subscribe** (lines 120-161): Subscribes to active round updates via `subscribeToRound()` → needs chain subscription\n4. **Join Round** (lines 164-189): Calls mock `joinRound()` → needs on-chain TX\n5. **Buy More** (lines 191-213): Calls mock `buyMoreEntries()` → needs on-chain TX\n6. **Claim Payout** (lines 215-240): Auto-claims on win → needs on-chain TX\n\n---\n\n### **4. Utilities**\n\n#### **Odds Calculation (`odds.ts`)**\n- ✅ **No mock here** — all deterministic math\n- Uses \"largest remainder method\" for fair rounding\n- Returns `PlayerOdds[]` with exact percentages summing to 100%\n- Used by wheel visualization to size player slots\n\n#### **Helper Functions (`mock-simulation.ts`)**\n```typescript\ntruncateAddress(address: string)         // Truncates address for display\ngetPlayerColor(index, isCurrentUser)     // Assigns colors from PLAYER_COLORS array\ncalculatePayout(poolAmount: number)      // Returns poolAmount * 0.97\ngenerateMockAddress()                    // Random address format (for mock players)\ngenerateMockHexString(length)            // Random hex for fair data (MOCK)\ngenerateFairnessData()                   // Generates fake seed/proof/blockhash (MOCK)\n```\n\n---\n\n### **5. Spec Contract (`docs/specs/101-lord-of-the-rngs/spec.md`)**\n\n**Key Requirements from Spec:**\n\n1. **Tier Amounts**: SOL values from `game-engine/types.ts` (0.005–1.0 SOL per tier)\n2. **Max Players**: 20 per round\n3. **Min Players to Start**: 2 unique players\n4. **Countdown Duration**: 60 seconds\n5. **Spin Trigger**: Any player can trigger after countdown expires (idempotent)\n6. **Winner Selection**: VRF determines slot (0 to totalEntries-1)\n7. **Payout**: 97% of pool (3% fee)\n8. **Claim Model**: Pull-based (`claim_payout` instruction)\n\n**Phases:**\n- **Waiting**: No countdown yet, joining enabled\n- **Countdown**: 60s timer, joining enabled, additional entries allowed\n- **Spinning**: Wheel animating, no new entries\n- **Revealing**: Show winner before auto-transition\n- **Complete**: Round settled, winner can claim\n\n---\n\n### **6. Components Overview**\n\n| Component | Purpose | Depends On |\n|-----------|---------|-----------|\n| `TierLobby.tsx` | Grid of 6 tier cards | `tierStatuses`, `setSelectedTier` |\n| `TierRoundView.tsx` | Individual tier status card | `TierStatus` type |\n| `ActiveRoundView.tsx` | Main game view when in round | `Round`, `WheelVisualization` |\n| `WheelVisualization.tsx` | Animated wheel rendering | `Round`, `calculateOdds()` |\n| `CountdownTimer.tsx` | 60s countdown display | `endsAt` timestamp |\n\n---\n\n### **Summary: What Needs Replacement**\n\n| Item | Current | Target |\n|------|---------|--------|\n| **Round Creation** | `createRound()` timer-based | `initialize_round` on-chain instruction |\n| **Join Round** | `joinRound()` in-memory | `join_round` on-chain instruction |\n| **Buy Entries** | `buyMoreEntries()` in-memory | `buy_more_entries` on-chain instruction |\n| **Phase Transitions** | `startCountdown()`, `startSpinning()` timer-based | On-chain instructions + event handlers |\n| **Winner Selection** | Random number (MOCK) | VRF callback result |\n| **Subscriptions** | In-memory listeners | Event stream subscription (RPC/Bankrun) |\n| **Auto-Claim** | Instant UI update | On-chain `claim_payout` TX + confirmation |\n| **Mock Players** | Can stay or be made toggleable | Client-side automation (optional) |\n\n---\n\n### **File Paths (Absolute)**\n\n- **Types**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/types.ts`\n- **Mock Simulation**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/utils/mock-simulation.ts`\n- **Context**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/context/LordOfRngsContext.tsx`\n- **Odds**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/utils/odds.ts`\n- **Components**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/components/`\n- **Spec**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/101-lord-of-the-rngs/spec.md`\n\nThis exploration reveals a clean mock architecture ready for chain integration. The main replacement work is connecting the context's async action functions to real on-chain instructions and replacing the in-memory store with on-chain state queries."}],"totalDurationMs":40136,"totalTokens":47438,"totalToolUseCount":13,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2585,"cache_read_input_tokens":41857,"output_tokens":2995,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2585,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BknEYWgxSCZjykHk8wfs2c","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have all the information you need. Let me provide you with a comprehensive analysis of the coinflip `chain.ts` pattern.\n\n---\n\n## Full Content of chain.ts\n\nSee above in the Read output (511 lines total). Here's the structure:\n\n---\n\n## Key Patterns & Architecture for Mirroring in Lord of the RNGs\n\n### 1. **Imports Structure**\n```typescript\n// Core: Anchor provider/program\nimport { Program, AnchorProvider, type Idl } from \"@coral-xyz/anchor\";\nimport { Connection, PublicKey, SystemProgram, Transaction } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n\n// Game-specific IDL (from anchor-client package)\nimport { CoinflipIDL, type Coinflip } from \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\";\n\n// Game engine constants (tier/side values, type definitions)\nimport {\n  TIER_VALUES,\n  COIN_SIDE_VALUES,\n  TIER_AMOUNTS,\n  type Tier,\n  type CoinSide,\n} from \"@rng-utopia/game-engine/browser\";\n\n// Local UI types\nimport type { UIMatch } from \"../types\";\n```\n\n**For Lord of the RNGs:** Replace `CoinflipIDL` with `LordOfTheRngsIDL` and import the equivalent game engine constants.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Program Setup Pattern**\n\n**Constants Section:**\n```typescript\nconst COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\n  (import.meta as unknown as { env: Record<string, string | undefined> }).env\n    .VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID ?? CoinflipIDL.address\n);\n\nconst ORAO_VRF_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\"VRFzZoJdhFWL8rkvu87LpKM3RbcVezpMEc6X5GVDr7y\");\n```\n\n**Read-only Program Instance:**\n```typescript\nfunction getCoinflipProgram(connection: Connection): Program<Coinflip> {\n  // Read-only provider (no wallet needed for queries)\n  const provider = new AnchorProvider(\n    connection,\n    {} as AnchorProvider[\"wallet\"],\n    { commitment: \"confirmed\" }\n  );\n  return new Program(CoinflipIDL as Idl as Coinflip, provider);\n}\n```\n\n**Pattern:** Read-only program instance created on-demand from connection. No wallet required for fetches.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **PDA Derivation Pattern**\n\n```typescript\n// ============ PDA Derivation ============\n\nexport function getMatchPda(creator: PublicKey): [PublicKey, number] {\n  return PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"match\"), creator.toBuffer()],\n    COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID\n  );\n}\n\nexport function getConfigPda(): [PublicKey, number] {\n  return PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"coinflip_config\")],\n    COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID\n  );\n}\n\n// External VRF PDAs\nfunction getOraoNetworkStatePda(): PublicKey {\n  const [pda] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"orao-vrf-network-configuration\")],\n    ORAO_VRF_PROGRAM_ID\n  );\n  return pda;\n}\n\nfunction getOraoRandomnessPda(seed: Uint8Array): PublicKey {\n  const [pda] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"orao-vrf-randomness-request\"), seed],\n    ORAO_VRF_PROGRAM_ID\n  );\n  return pda;\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- Derive PDAs using `findProgramAddressSync` with seed buffers\n- Use specific string keys (e.g., `\"match\"`, `\"coinflip_config\"`)\n- Return tuple `[pda, bump]` from Anchor's method, but only use the pda in exports\n- External program PDAs (Orao VRF) also derived here\n\n---\n\n### 4. **On-Chain Account Type Definition**\n\n```typescript\ntype RoundPhaseVariant = \n  | { waiting: object } \n  | { active: object } \n  | { locked: object }\n  | { resolving: object } \n  | { settled: object } \n  | { refunded: object };\n\ninterface OnChainMatch {\n  creator: PublicKey;\n  opponent: PublicKey;\n  tier: number;\n  entryAmount: { toNumber(): number };\n  creatorSide: number;\n  phase: RoundPhaseVariant;\n  result: number;\n  winner: PublicKey;\n  claimed: boolean;\n  createdAt: { toNumber(): number };\n  lockedAt: { toNumber(): number };\n  resolveDeadline: { toNumber(): number };\n  vrfRequestKey: PublicKey;\n  bump: number;\n}\n```\n\n**Pattern:** Type-cast fetched accounts to this shape with `as unknown as OnChainMatch`.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Converter Functions (On-Chain → UI)**\n\n```typescript\n// Index/enum converters\nfunction tierFromIndex(index: number): Tier {\n  const tiers: Tier[] = [\"iron\", \"bronze\", \"silver\", \"gold\", \"platinum\", \"diamond\"];\n  return tiers[index] ?? \"iron\";\n}\n\nfunction sideFromIndex(index: number): CoinSide {\n  return index === 0 ? \"heads\" : \"tails\";\n}\n\n// Phase & validation helpers\nfunction isPhase(phase: RoundPhaseVariant, name: string): boolean {\n  return name in phase;\n}\n\nfunction phaseToUI(phase: RoundPhaseVariant): UIMatch[\"phase\"] {\n  if (isPhase(phase, \"waiting\")) return \"created\";\n  if (isPhase(phase, \"locked\")) return \"ready\";\n  if (isPhase(phase, \"settled\")) return \"complete\";\n  return \"created\";\n}\n\nfunction isDefaultPubkey(key: PublicKey): boolean {\n  return key.equals(PublicKey.default);\n}\n\n// Main converter: OnChainMatch → UIMatch\nexport function onChainMatchToUI(\n  matchPda: PublicKey,\n  data: OnChainMatch\n): UIMatch {\n  const tier = tierFromIndex(data.tier);\n  const creatorSide = sideFromIndex(data.creatorSide);\n  const hasOpponent = !isDefaultPubkey(data.opponent);\n  const phase = phaseToUI(data.phase);\n  const isSettled = isPhase(data.phase, \"settled\");\n\n  const entryAmountSol = TIER_AMOUNTS[tier];\n  const totalPool = entryAmountSol * 2;\n  const payoutAmount = totalPool * 0.97;\n\n  const lockedAt = data.lockedAt.toNumber();\n\n  return {\n    id: matchPda.toBase58(),\n    tier,\n    entryAmount: entryAmountSol,\n    player1: data.creator.toBase58(),\n    player1Side: creatorSide,\n    player2: hasOpponent ? data.opponent.toBase58() : null,\n    player2Side: hasOpponent\n      ? (creatorSide === \"heads\" ? \"tails\" : \"heads\")\n      : null,\n    phase,\n    createdAt: Date.now(),\n    lockedAt: lockedAt > 0 ? lockedAt * 1000 : undefined,\n    result: isSettled ? sideFromIndex(data.result) : null,\n    winner: isSettled && !isDefaultPubkey(data.winner)\n      ? data.winner.toBase58()\n      : null,\n    claimed: data.claimed,\n    payoutAmount,\n    seedHash: \"\",\n  };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. **VRF Randomness Reading Pattern**\n\n```typescript\n/** Read fulfilled VRF randomness bytes from an Orao randomness account.\n *  Returns the first randomness byte (used for coin flip result) or null if not fulfilled. */\nasync function readVrfRandomness(\n  connection: Connection,\n  vrfRequestKey: PublicKey\n): Promise<number | null> {\n  try {\n    if (isDefaultPubkey(vrfRequestKey)) return null;\n    const vrfAccount = await connection.getAccountInfo(vrfRequestKey);\n    if (vrfAccount && vrfAccount.data.length > 8) {\n      // Orao randomness account: 8-byte discriminator then randomness data.\n      const randomnessData = vrfAccount.data.subarray(8, 72);\n      if (randomnessData.some((b: number) => b !== 0)) {\n        return randomnessData[0] ?? null;\n      }\n    }\n  } catch {\n    // Ignore — treat as not fulfilled\n  }\n  return null;\n}\n```\n\n**Pattern:** Read raw account data, check for non-zero bytes to detect fulfillment, extract first byte.\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Account Fetch Patterns**\n\n**Fetch all open matches (with filter):**\n```typescript\nexport async function fetchAllOpenMatches(\n  connection: Connection\n): Promise<UIMatch[]> {\n  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n  const accounts = await program.account.coinflipMatch.all();\n\n  return accounts\n    .filter((acc) => isPhase((acc.account as unknown as OnChainMatch).phase, \"waiting\"))\n    .map((acc) =>\n      onChainMatchToUI(\n        acc.publicKey,\n        acc.account as unknown as OnChainMatch\n      )\n    );\n}\n```\n\n**Fetch with on-chain filters (memcmp for efficiency):**\n```typescript\nexport async function fetchClaimableMatches(\n  connection: Connection,\n  playerPubkey: PublicKey\n): Promise<UIMatch[]> {\n  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n  const playerBase58 = playerPubkey.toBase58();\n\n  // claimed == false: single byte 0x00, base58-encoded as \"1\"\n  const claimedFalseFilter = { memcmp: { offset: 116, bytes: \"1\" } };\n\n  const [asCreator, asOpponent] = await Promise.all([\n    program.account.coinflipMatch.all([\n      { memcmp: { offset: 8, bytes: playerBase58 } },\n      claimedFalseFilter,\n    ]),\n    program.account.coinflipMatch.all([\n      { memcmp: { offset: 40, bytes: playerBase58 } },\n      claimedFalseFilter,\n    ]),\n  ]);\n\n  // Merge and deduplicate by public key\n  const seen = new Set<string>();\n  const matches: UIMatch[] = [];\n\n  for (const acc of [...asCreator, ...asOpponent]) {\n    const key = acc.publicKey.toBase58();\n    if (seen.has(key)) continue;\n    seen.add(key);\n\n    const data = acc.account as unknown as OnChainMatch;\n    // Skip terminal phase (refunded)\n    if (isPhase(data.phase, \"refunded\")) continue;\n\n    const match = onChainMatchToUI(acc.publicKey, data);\n\n    // Upgrade Locked → complete when VRF has resolved, deriving winner client-side\n    const vrfByte = isPhase(data.phase, \"locked\")\n      ? await readVrfRandomness(connection, data.vrfRequestKey)\n      : null;\n    if (vrfByte !== null) {\n      const derived = deriveWinnerFromVrf(vrfByte, data);\n      matches.push({ ...match, phase: \"complete\", result: derived.result, winner: derived.winner });\n    } else {\n      matches.push(match);\n    }\n  }\n\n  return matches;\n}\n```\n\n**Key technique:** Use `memcmp` filters with exact byte offsets from account layout. Account names are base58-encoded for string fields.\n\n**Fetch single match by PDA:**\n```typescript\nexport async function fetchMatchByCreator(\n  connection: Connection,\n  creator: PublicKey\n): Promise<UIMatch | null> {\n  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n  const [matchPda] = getMatchPda(creator);\n\n  try {\n    const account = await program.account.coinflipMatch.fetch(matchPda);\n    const data = account as unknown as OnChainMatch;\n    const match = onChainMatchToUI(matchPda, data);\n    // ... VRF upgrade logic ...\n    return match;\n  } catch {\n    // Account doesn't exist\n    return null;\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Transaction Building Pattern**\n\nAll transaction builders follow this signature:\n\n```typescript\nexport async function build<ActionName>Tx(\n  connection: Connection,\n  caller: PublicKey,\n  // ... other params specific to action\n): Promise<Transaction> {\n  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n  \n  // Derive all PDAs needed for the instruction\n  const [matchPda] = getMatchPda(matchCreator);\n  const [configPda] = getConfigPda();\n  // ... other derivations ...\n\n  // Build instruction via Anchor methods\n  const ix = await program.methods\n    .<methodName>()\n    .accountsStrict({\n      caller,\n      coinflipMatch: matchPda,\n      config: configPda,\n      systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n      // ... all required accounts ...\n    })\n    .instruction();\n\n  // Create unsigned transaction\n  const tx = new Transaction().add(ix);\n  tx.feePayer = caller;\n  tx.recentBlockhash = (await connection.getLatestBlockhash()).blockhash;\n\n  return tx;\n}\n```\n\n**Examples:**\n\n**Create match:**\n```typescript\nexport async function buildCreateMatchTx(\n  connection: Connection,\n  creator: PublicKey,\n  tier: Tier,\n  side: CoinSide\n): Promise<{ transaction: Transaction; matchPda: PublicKey }> {\n  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n  const [matchPda] = getMatchPda(creator);\n  const [configPda] = getConfigPda();\n\n  const tierIndex = TIER_VALUES[tier];\n  const sideIndex = COIN_SIDE_VALUES[side];\n\n  const ix = await program.methods\n    .createMatch(tierIndex, sideIndex)\n    .accountsStrict({\n      creator,\n      coinflipMatch: matchPda,\n      config: configPda,\n      systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n    })\n    .instruction();\n\n  const tx = new Transaction().add(ix);\n  tx.feePayer = creator;\n  tx.recentBlockhash = (await connection.getLatestBlockhash()).blockhash;\n\n  return { transaction: tx, matchPda };\n}\n```\n\n**Join match (complex with VRF):**\n```typescript\nexport async function buildJoinMatchTx(\n  connection: Connection,\n  opponent: PublicKey,\n  matchCreator: PublicKey\n): Promise<Transaction> {\n  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n  const [matchPda] = getMatchPda(matchCreator);\n  const [configPda] = getConfigPda();\n\n  // Fetch Orao VRF network state to extract treasury address\n  const oraoNetworkState = getOraoNetworkStatePda();\n  const networkInfo = await connection.getAccountInfo(oraoNetworkState);\n  if (!networkInfo) throw new Error(\"Orao VRF network state not found on-chain\");\n  // Treasury is at offset 40 in Orao NetworkState (8-byte discriminator + 32-byte authority)\n  const oraoTreasury = new PublicKey(networkInfo.data.subarray(40, 72));\n  const oraoRandom = getOraoRandomnessPda(matchPda.toBytes());\n\n  const ix = await program.methods\n    .joinMatch()\n    .accountsStrict({\n      opponent,\n      coinflipMatch: matchPda,\n      config: configPda,\n      oraoProgram: ORAO_VRF_PROGRAM_ID,\n      oraoNetworkState,\n      oraoTreasury,\n      oraoRandom,\n      systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n    })\n    .instruction();\n\n  const tx = new Transaction().add(ix);\n  tx.feePayer = opponent;\n  tx.recentBlockhash = (await connection.getLatestBlockhash()).blockhash;\n\n  return tx;\n}\n```\n\n**Claim payout (with CPI to platform program):**\n```typescript\nexport async function buildClaimPayoutTx(\n  connection: Connection,\n  caller: PublicKey,\n  matchCreator: PublicKey,\n  opponent: PublicKey\n): Promise<Transaction> {\n  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n  const [matchPda] = getMatchPda(matchCreator);\n  const [configPda] = getConfigPda();\n\n  // Fetch config to get treasury address\n  const config = await program.account.coinflipConfig.fetch(configPda);\n  const treasury = (config as unknown as { treasury: PublicKey }).treasury;\n\n  // Derive randomness account from match PDA (VRF seed = match PDA key)\n  const randomnessAccount = getOraoRandomnessPda(matchPda.toBytes());\n\n  // Derive player profile PDAs for CPI\n  const PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\n    (import.meta as unknown as { env: Record<string, string | undefined> }).env\n      .VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID ?? \"85qwC1cDpSYkBBHUcN4nuZ119hCx4N94X38GjAHxnWjA\"\n  );\n  const [creatorProfile] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"player_profile\"), matchCreator.toBuffer()],\n    PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID\n  );\n  const [opponentProfile] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"player_profile\"), opponent.toBuffer()],\n    PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID\n  );\n\n  const ix = await program.methods\n    .claimPayout()\n    .accountsStrict({\n      caller,\n      coinflipMatch: matchPda,\n      config: configPda,\n      treasury,\n      creator: matchCreator,\n      opponent,\n      randomnessAccount,\n      creatorProfile,\n      opponentProfile,\n      platformProgram: PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID,\n      systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n    })\n    .instruction();\n\n  const tx = new Transaction().add(ix);\n  tx.feePayer = caller;\n  tx.recentBlockhash = (await connection.getLatestBlockhash()).blockhash;\n\n  return tx;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Export Summary**\n\n**Exported Functions:**\n- `getMatchPda()` — Derive match PDA by creator\n- `getConfigPda()` — Derive config PDA\n- `onChainMatchToUI()` — Convert on-chain match to UI type\n- `fetchAllOpenMatches()` — Fetch all matches in \"waiting\" phase\n- `fetchClaimableMatches()` — Fetch all matches for a player with unclaimed payouts\n- `fetchMatchByCreator()` — Fetch single match by creator's PDA\n- `fetchMatch()` — Fetch single match by PDA directly\n- `buildCreateMatchTx()` — Build create-match transaction\n- `buildJoinMatchTx()` — Build join-match transaction\n- `buildCancelMatchTx()` — Build cancel-match transaction\n- `buildTimeoutCancelTx()` — Build timeout-cancel transaction\n- `buildClaimPayoutTx()` — Build claim-payout transaction\n\n**Internal (not exported):**\n- `getCoinflipProgram()` — Create read-only program instance\n- `getOraoNetworkStatePda()`, `getOraoRandomnessPda()` — VRF PDAs\n- `readVrfRandomness()` — Read VRF fulfillment\n- `deriveWinnerFromVrf()` — Client-side winner derivation\n- Helper converters and validators\n\n---\n\n## Summary for Lord of the RNGs\n\nTo mirror this pattern for Lord of the RNGs, you'll need to:\n\n1. **Replace game-specific constants:** `CoinflipIDL` → `LordOfTheRngsIDL`, program ID env var\n2. **Update PDA seed strings:** Change `\"match\"` to whatever your contract uses (e.g., `\"game_round\"`)\n3. **Define on-chain type shape:** Match your contract's `Round`/`Game` struct layout\n4. **Write converters:** Index → enum, on-chain → UI\n5. **Implement fetch functions:** Use same `program.account.<name>.all()` and `.fetch()` patterns with memcmp filters\n6. **Build transaction builders:** Follow the same Anchor `.methods.<name>().accountsStrict({...}).instruction()` pattern\n7. **Handle VRF if needed:** If using same Orao VRF, reuse those PDA derivations; if different RNG, adjust accordingly\n\nThe structure is **game-agnostic** — only the names, seed strings, and specific instruction/account signatures change."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a0c17d3 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 42004\ntool_uses: 7\nduration_ms: 54309</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8e5d7c3d-ef66-4971-8f66-de7d7c43ed7c","uuid":"25da84f7-5d31-491a-be29-9638a90f1b62","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the pattern used in the coinflip game's chain.ts file so I can mirror it for the Lord of the RNGs game. \n\nPlease find and read:\n1. The coinflip `chain.ts` file in `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/